WEBVTT

00:01.710 --> 00:03.128
<i>- Previously on "You"...</i>

00:03.128 --> 00:04.586
<i>- I love our little routine.
</i>- [moans]

00:04.586 --> 00:06.798
<i>- Always the same,
but never stale.</i>

00:06.798 --> 00:08.465
<i>Your father was
never consistent,</i>

00:08.465 --> 00:09.968
<i>and you're still healing
from that with my help.</i>

00:09.968 --> 00:11.553
<i>And guess what.</i>

00:11.553 --> 00:12.971
<i>Now that I've made
our morning sacred,</i>

00:12.971 --> 00:14.805
<i>you're actually writing.</i>

00:14.805 --> 00:17.225
<i>One day,
I'll tell you about Candace.</i>

00:17.225 --> 00:18.600
<i>She broke my heart.
</i>- [laughs]

00:18.600 --> 00:20.562
<i>- But you are good.</i>

00:20.562 --> 00:23.147
<i>You make cheating
a distant memory.</i>

00:23.147 --> 00:25.483
<i>Peach is taking you
out of town.</i>

00:25.483 --> 00:26.650
<i>I need to save you.</i>

00:28.027 --> 00:30.321
[tires screeching, crash]

00:31.489 --> 00:33.408
<i>- License and registration.</i>

00:33.408 --> 00:34.658
- Sorry, Spencer Hewitt.

00:34.658 --> 00:36.118
<i>- Dispatch to Nico,</i>

00:36.118 --> 00:38.496
<i>car's registered
to an Ivan Mooney.</i>

00:38.496 --> 00:39.706
- Kicked Ron out.

00:39.706 --> 00:41.374
You're right,
people don't change.

00:41.374 --> 00:43.125
<i>- Peach has it out for me.</i>

00:43.125 --> 00:44.918
<i>If I just keep being
the perfect boyfriend,</i>

00:44.918 --> 00:46.920
<i>you'll realize that life
is so much healthier</i>

00:46.920 --> 00:48.756
<i>away from this toxicity.</i>

00:48.756 --> 00:50.633
- You have issues, okay?

00:50.633 --> 00:51.926
Don't make your desperate,

00:51.926 --> 00:54.137
unending need for attention
about me.

00:54.137 --> 00:56.305
<i>- It's freeing in a way
to know for certain</i>

00:56.305 --> 00:57.973
<i>what I have to do
to protect you.</i>

00:57.973 --> 00:59.183
- Anyone here?

00:59.183 --> 01:01.101
<i>- I would do anything for you.</i>

01:01.101 --> 01:04.105
[both grunting]

01:04.105 --> 01:06.608
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:06.608 --> 01:08.902
[gunshot]

01:08.902 --> 01:10.403
<i>I'm not a bad person.</i>

01:10.403 --> 01:11.945
<i>She was going to ruin you.</i>

01:11.945 --> 01:14.573
<i>You're safe now, next to me.</i>

01:14.573 --> 01:16.117
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:18.745 --> 01:21.748
<i>[soft, dramatic music]</i>

01:21.748 --> 01:24.959
<i>That first perfect month--</i>

01:24.959 --> 01:28.045
<i>we'd been to hell and back,
we'd done the hard work,</i>

01:28.045 --> 01:29.671
<i>and we were closer than ever,</i>

01:29.671 --> 01:30.757
<i>we were living the dream.</i>

01:32.424 --> 01:33.968
<i>Couldn't keep our hands
off each other,</i>

01:33.968 --> 01:36.262
<i>couldn't keep anything
off each other.</i>

01:36.262 --> 01:38.972
<i>I was ready to wait it out
during the grief period,</i>

01:38.972 --> 01:40.098
<i>no matter what
that looked like.</i>

01:42.477 --> 01:44.813
<i>But it only brought us
closer together.</i>

01:46.772 --> 01:50.984
That month after
the funeral was--

01:50.984 --> 01:52.945
it was intimate.

01:52.945 --> 01:54.155
Real.

01:56.658 --> 02:00.411
Just made us more.

02:00.411 --> 02:03.121
<i>- No doubt,
awash with champagne...</i>

02:03.121 --> 02:04.790
<i>- But then, over the next
few weeks...</i>

02:04.790 --> 02:06.167
<i>[uneasy electronic music]</i>

02:06.167 --> 02:08.002
<i>Something happened.</i>

02:08.002 --> 02:14.550
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:14.550 --> 02:16.009
- Falafel.

02:18.096 --> 02:19.597
<i>- Couldn't tell you
the exact moment</i>

02:19.597 --> 02:21.181
<i>things went wrong between us.</i>

02:21.181 --> 02:22.933
But, uh,

02:22.933 --> 02:24.936
wrong they have gone.

02:27.187 --> 02:30.024
- So that's why
you're here in therapy, to...

02:30.024 --> 02:32.235
find out why your relationship
went south?

02:32.235 --> 02:34.570
- Oh, it didn't just go south.

02:34.570 --> 02:35.697
It's over.

02:37.031 --> 02:38.574
And I wanna know why.

02:38.574 --> 02:41.578
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

02:41.578 --> 02:48.626
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:50.002 --> 02:52.045
- Listen, here's the deal.

02:52.045 --> 02:55.258
Don't think of this as
an office or me as a shrink.

02:55.258 --> 02:58.051
We're just two dudes,
you know, shooting the shit.

02:59.262 --> 03:00.930
Why don't we start...
[recorder beeps]

03:00.930 --> 03:03.891
When things were good
with you two?

03:03.891 --> 03:07.186
<i>- Hmm, my first kiss?
Good question.</i>

03:07.186 --> 03:09.980
I was 14, and I was going out

03:09.980 --> 03:13.359
with this, um, boy Matt.

03:13.359 --> 03:15.652
<i>- You know, we told each other
all the good stuff.</i>

03:15.652 --> 03:18.531
- He was so sweet,
and we went to see, um,

03:18.531 --> 03:22.075
"Hitch" together...
[laughs]

03:22.075 --> 03:24.245
And I was waiting for him
to make the move.

03:24.245 --> 03:27.122
- Waiting--so, what,
that was your first kiss?

03:27.122 --> 03:31.169
- No, it was two nights later
on a school camping trip,

03:31.169 --> 03:33.879
in a tent in the rain,

03:33.879 --> 03:35.465
with his best friend, Chad.

03:35.465 --> 03:38.425
- Oh, Chad.
- I know.

03:38.425 --> 03:39.968
- Chad.
- I know.

03:39.968 --> 03:43.680
[laughs] I mean, but Chad,
he just--he went for it,

03:43.680 --> 03:45.599
and I've always had trouble
with that kind of thing,

03:45.599 --> 03:49.562
the whole good guy
versus bad boy bit.

03:49.562 --> 03:51.146
Don't look at me that way.

03:51.146 --> 03:53.858
Trust me,
I wish I could have a redo.

03:53.858 --> 03:56.526
I still feel like
a hootsie for it.

03:56.526 --> 03:58.987
- A hootsie?

03:58.987 --> 04:00.073
That should totally be a word.

04:00.073 --> 04:01.115
- [laughs]

04:02.157 --> 04:03.659
No real words?

04:03.659 --> 04:05.620
- Only fake ones.
- [laughs]

04:05.620 --> 04:07.163
- Punklassical.
- Photobomb.

04:07.163 --> 04:09.957
Ravey.
<i> - We connected on every level.</i>

04:09.957 --> 04:10.959
<i>It doesn't get any better.</i>

04:10.959 --> 04:13.544
- Everythingship.

04:13.544 --> 04:15.504
I love that.

04:15.504 --> 04:18.132
It's like our word.

04:18.132 --> 04:19.800
Everythingship.

04:19.800 --> 04:21.802
And now...

04:21.802 --> 04:24.137
- A meeting of the minds,

04:24.137 --> 04:27.307
bodies, and souls.

04:27.307 --> 04:29.851
<i>[mellow pop music]</i>

04:29.851 --> 04:31.478
<i>Okay, Beck, ready?</i>

04:31.478 --> 04:32.730
[door creaks]

04:32.730 --> 04:34.314
♪ ♪

04:34.314 --> 04:35.817
- Wha...

04:35.817 --> 04:37.694
[laughs]

04:37.694 --> 04:40.487
It can't be.

04:40.487 --> 04:42.949
Are we redoing my first kiss?

04:42.949 --> 04:45.326
- We're redoing
your first kiss.

04:45.326 --> 04:47.370
- Wow.

04:47.370 --> 04:50.540
I'm finally gonna kiss
the right guy.

04:50.540 --> 04:54.543
<i>- It was an everythingship,
it really was.</i>

04:54.543 --> 04:56.920
We were in a really
healthy place.

04:56.920 --> 04:58.880
I mean, I'd even stopped

04:58.880 --> 05:02.218
<i>relying on the, you know,
like, these certain crutches.</i>

05:02.218 --> 05:04.220
- Crutches?
- Yeah.

05:04.220 --> 05:05.971
<i>Checking social media,</i>

05:05.971 --> 05:08.098
<i>sneaking a peek at
a locked screen and--</i>

05:08.098 --> 05:11.351
it was time to stop
'cause we were real.

05:11.351 --> 05:13.687
I just needed to--
- Trust?

05:15.314 --> 05:17.108
- Sure.

05:17.108 --> 05:18.942
I'll see you after work.

05:18.942 --> 05:20.569
- Yeah, about that.

05:20.569 --> 05:24.365
I may have gotten fired
from the yoga studio.

05:25.824 --> 05:27.117
- May have?
- Oh...

05:27.117 --> 05:30.538
I got fired.

05:30.538 --> 05:33.290
Apparently I fell asleep
leading Savasana.

05:33.290 --> 05:34.709
- [snickers]

05:34.709 --> 05:36.793
- It's fine.
I can find another job.

05:36.793 --> 05:38.754
I can...
- Come work at Mooney's.

05:38.754 --> 05:40.380
<i>I know, I know. Big step.</i>

05:40.380 --> 05:41.423
- Joe.

05:41.423 --> 05:43.050
- Come on, it's perfect.

05:43.050 --> 05:45.302
Flexible hours,
you have time to write.

05:45.302 --> 05:46.553
I wanna help.

05:46.553 --> 05:48.889
- I can't ask that of you.

05:48.889 --> 05:51.225
- Well, you're not asking,
I'm offering.

05:51.225 --> 05:54.853
<i>But big steps feel right
in an everythingship.</i>

05:54.853 --> 05:56.564
<i>- Yeah, yeah, I get that.</i>

06:00.942 --> 06:02.737
Oh, don't worry about this.

06:02.737 --> 06:04.822
I'm in early stages
of asymptomatic glaucoma,

06:04.822 --> 06:06.449
so I got a prescription.

06:06.449 --> 06:09.035
I swear, this makes me
such a better listener.

06:09.035 --> 06:11.411
They should do a study.

06:11.411 --> 06:14.331
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

06:14.331 --> 06:18.002
[inhaling]

06:18.002 --> 06:20.629
[exhaling]

06:20.629 --> 06:23.132
[sighs]
So what happened next?

06:23.132 --> 06:24.591
<i>- Ooh, hey, Ethan?</i>

06:24.591 --> 06:27.220
Do you mind taking
a picture of us?

06:27.220 --> 06:31.432
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:31.432 --> 06:33.266
- [sighs]
Uh, I'm sorry,

06:33.266 --> 06:34.601
I think I just need
to sit down.

06:34.601 --> 06:37.271
I, um, pre-gamed
the new Safran Foer

06:37.271 --> 06:38.730
by reading "Eating Animals,"

06:38.730 --> 06:40.483
and I'm test driving
veganism now,

06:40.483 --> 06:42.276
and I'm just feeling
a little faint.

06:42.276 --> 06:43.360
both: Oh.

06:43.360 --> 06:46.029
- [laughs]
Of course.

06:46.029 --> 06:47.740
[shutter clicks]

06:47.740 --> 06:50.201
- You two are
absolutely adorable,

06:50.201 --> 06:54.454
and I am a lonely
vegan island.

06:55.497 --> 06:56.874
- Someone needs a burger.

06:56.874 --> 07:00.043
- Or somewhere to put his meat.

07:00.043 --> 07:02.629
- Oh.
- Okay, that was bad.

07:02.629 --> 07:04.714
I meant it sympathetically.

07:04.714 --> 07:06.716
<i>[gentle string music]</i>

07:06.716 --> 07:07.968
- We have a hashtag now?

07:07.968 --> 07:09.971
- Too much?
- It's perfect.

07:09.971 --> 07:12.348
<i>What happened next
was we were doing great.</i>

07:12.348 --> 07:15.810
<i>It was safe to open up
about the very hardest things.</i>

07:15.810 --> 07:17.562
- You know, uh,

07:17.562 --> 07:20.814
Peach went on a date
with JSF in high school.

07:20.814 --> 07:23.651
<i>- I thought that grief
was really the last frontier.</i>

07:23.651 --> 07:25.610
- Apparently,
he ate pork belly.

07:25.610 --> 07:27.446
Very scandalous.

07:27.446 --> 07:30.074
And Peach always said th--

07:30.074 --> 07:32.451
um...
[laughs]

07:32.451 --> 07:34.829
- You can talk about her,
you know.

07:34.829 --> 07:36.329
- Yeah, I know.

07:36.329 --> 07:38.415
- You haven't mentioned her
since the funeral.

07:38.415 --> 07:40.084
It's been over a month.

07:40.084 --> 07:41.961
<i>And we were at that
frontier together.</i>

07:41.961 --> 07:43.920
- Actually, I think I--

07:43.920 --> 07:46.548
I'd rather save it for therapy,
if that's okay.

07:46.548 --> 07:48.718
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

07:48.718 --> 07:50.261
- Therapy?

07:50.261 --> 07:52.012
<i>Except, it turns out,
we weren't.</i>

07:52.012 --> 07:55.557
- Yeah, I--I used to go
about a year ago,

07:55.557 --> 07:57.018
but I stopped,
but then after Peach,

07:57.018 --> 07:59.353
I thought it was worth it

07:59.353 --> 08:03.064
to go for a bit.

08:03.064 --> 08:04.274
I mean, honestly,

08:04.274 --> 08:05.735
Dr. Nicky's been really helpful

08:05.735 --> 08:08.362
dealing with my grief.

08:08.362 --> 08:09.779
I think we need more stars.

08:09.779 --> 08:11.865
They're in your office, right?
- Yeah.

08:11.865 --> 08:13.367
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:13.367 --> 08:15.202
<i>Don't get me wrong...
[stammers]</i>

08:15.202 --> 08:16.661
<i>There's nothing wrong
with going to therapy,</i>

08:16.661 --> 08:18.413
<i>it's just,
it's a bit troubling</i>

08:18.413 --> 08:20.207
<i>when your partner
hides something from you.</i>

08:21.209 --> 08:23.920
Don't you agree, Dr. Nicky?

08:23.920 --> 08:25.213
- I hear you, Paul.

08:25.213 --> 08:27.048
Not cool.

08:27.048 --> 08:28.966
<i>- Forgive me, Beck,
but for the purposes</i>

08:28.966 --> 08:30.718
<i>of this session
with your therapist,</i>

08:30.718 --> 08:32.720
<i>you are Renaldo...
- [echoing speech]</i>

08:32.720 --> 08:35.472
<i>- Tall, dark, and man-bunned
backup dancer for Beyoncé,</i>

08:35.472 --> 08:37.350
<i>and I, Paul,
well, I manage a bar.</i>

08:37.350 --> 08:38.893
<i>Every asshole in this city</i>

08:38.893 --> 08:40.644
<i>has the same
not-so-special problems.</i>

08:40.644 --> 08:43.730
<i>It won't be hard
to hide who I am.</i>

08:43.730 --> 08:45.816
- You two seem
pretty copacetic,

08:45.816 --> 08:47.567
sort of, uh...

08:47.567 --> 08:50.738
things were Ross and Rachel
with you and Renaldo.

08:50.738 --> 08:52.490
- Yeah.

08:52.490 --> 08:55.533
I guess they--they were,

08:55.533 --> 08:56.994
until they weren't.

08:56.994 --> 08:58.828
<i>See, I thought
I'd eliminated all</i>

08:58.828 --> 09:01.957
<i>the obstacles between us--
Beck, Benji, Peach--</i>

09:01.957 --> 09:04.460
<i>but now another
has reared its head,</i>

09:04.460 --> 09:06.879
<i>and he's sitting
right in front of me.</i>

09:12.592 --> 09:14.928
- All right, Paul,
let's keep digging into this.

09:14.928 --> 09:16.931
All right, tell me,
when did you see

09:16.931 --> 09:19.307
the first cracks
with Renaldo?

09:19.307 --> 09:22.602
<i>[soft, dramatic music]</i>

09:22.602 --> 09:25.022
<i>- Well, having Renaldo
at work was amazing,</i>

09:25.022 --> 09:28.109
<i>but it did force me
to confront some slightly</i>

09:28.109 --> 09:31.445
<i>careless aspects
of his personality.</i>

09:31.445 --> 09:38.451
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:38.451 --> 09:40.578
<i>I tried to cut him
some slack--</i>

09:40.578 --> 09:43.290
<i>you know, new job--
and somewhere in there,</i>

09:43.290 --> 09:45.459
<i>he's still grieving, right?</i>

09:45.459 --> 09:47.753
- [clears throat]
- Hey.

09:47.753 --> 09:50.338
- We need to talk.
- About what?

09:50.338 --> 09:53.466
- Look, this is uncomfortable,
she's your girlfriend,

09:53.466 --> 09:55.885
and lord knows I'm not
one to criticize,

09:55.885 --> 09:58.596
but Becky's terrible, Joe.

09:58.596 --> 10:00.890
Okay? She's always late,
she leaves the register open,

10:00.890 --> 10:03.019
she doesn't know
how to organize by genre.

10:03.019 --> 10:04.729
Just this morning,
she chewed out

10:04.729 --> 10:06.813
a 14-year-old for buying
"American Tragedy" for school

10:06.813 --> 10:08.024
because she hates Dreiser.

10:08.024 --> 10:09.942
Everyone hates Dreiser.

10:09.942 --> 10:12.278
But this is a bookstore, okay?
We're trying to sell books.

10:12.278 --> 10:14.029
And I hear you, buddy.

10:14.029 --> 10:16.657
You're caught up hard
in the Tilt-A-Whirl of punani,

10:16.657 --> 10:18.616
and that is something
I struggle with every day.

10:18.616 --> 10:20.161
But here's the thing, brother.

10:20.161 --> 10:23.496
Shitting where you eat
just leads to confusion

10:23.496 --> 10:25.081
and E. coli.

10:26.458 --> 10:29.253
So I'm gonna let you ruminate
on that for a little bit.

10:30.671 --> 10:33.173
<i>- Yeah, well,
we were a little imperfect.</i>

10:33.173 --> 10:35.176
[phone rings]

10:35.176 --> 10:37.219
<i>But I still thought
we were in great shape,</i>

10:37.219 --> 10:39.179
<i>if that was the worst
of our problems.</i>

10:39.179 --> 10:43.058
<i>[tense music]</i>

10:43.058 --> 10:46.519
[coughs, clears throat]

10:46.519 --> 10:48.688
Mooney's, rare and used.

10:48.688 --> 10:51.149
- This is Officer Nico,
Greenwich Sheriff's Department.

10:51.149 --> 10:54.195
I'm looking for
a Mr. Ivan Mooney.

10:54.195 --> 10:55.863
- Speaking.

10:55.863 --> 10:57.865
<i>- Calling about a Buick
registered to your name.</i>

10:57.865 --> 11:00.493
- Yeah, I gave that car
to my nephew, Spencer.

11:00.493 --> 11:02.202
<i>Is he in trouble?</i>

11:02.202 --> 11:04.205
- [laughs softly] No.

11:04.205 --> 11:06.874
<i>I was just calling about
a little fender bender he had.</i>

11:06.874 --> 11:09.250
<i>It was nothing.
Have a nice day.</i>

11:09.250 --> 11:11.253
<i>[tense music]</i>

11:11.253 --> 11:13.172
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:13.172 --> 11:14.548
- That was too close.

11:14.548 --> 11:17.551
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:17.551 --> 11:20.888
<i>I just saw my job as keeping
the outside world away</i>

11:20.888 --> 11:22.389
<i>so Renaldo could heal.</i>

11:22.389 --> 11:25.725
Hey, Ethan said
you were late again today.

11:25.725 --> 11:28.395
- Yeah, I know. Sorry.

11:28.395 --> 11:31.856
<i>- It was hard to find a line
between boss and boyfriend,</i>

11:31.856 --> 11:34.067
<i>between supporting
and enabling.</i>

11:34.067 --> 11:36.903
- But you did say
the hours were flexible

11:36.903 --> 11:38.697
and that I'd have
time to write.

11:38.697 --> 11:42.076
- I did,
but you haven't been writing.

11:42.076 --> 11:44.620
- Thinking about writing
is a part of the process.

11:46.746 --> 11:48.540
Okay, that sounded
like bullshit,

11:48.540 --> 11:51.418
even as I said it.

11:51.418 --> 11:52.919
I'm sorry.

11:52.919 --> 11:55.505
The truth is...

11:55.505 --> 11:58.759
I've been having really
vivid dreams about Peach.

12:00.760 --> 12:02.638
- I'm sorry about that.

12:02.638 --> 12:05.432
- It's not your fault,
it's just...

12:05.432 --> 12:09.144
her face, it's...fading,

12:09.144 --> 12:13.731
and I didn't think
that would happen so fast.

12:13.731 --> 12:16.110
But she comes at night, so,

12:16.110 --> 12:20.780
now I am too tired to write
and falling behind at school,

12:20.780 --> 12:24.784
and now I'm failing you
by being bad at this job.

12:24.784 --> 12:27.288
<i>- I couldn't tell if I was
helping; I thought I was.</i>

12:27.288 --> 12:29.706
- It's pathetic--
the only good thing

12:29.706 --> 12:31.708
in my life right now
is therapy.

12:32.750 --> 12:34.461
- That's the only good thing?

12:34.461 --> 12:36.963
- Joe, don't be like that.

12:36.963 --> 12:38.756
<i>- Or I was totally wrong,
and there were</i>

12:38.756 --> 12:41.634
<i>dark forces at work
I wasn't privy to.</i>

12:41.634 --> 12:43.511
<i>[loud knocking]
- Claudia!</i>

12:43.511 --> 12:46.307
<i>- There are people who
are thoroughly delusional</i>

12:46.307 --> 12:48.142
<i>about their relationship.
</i>- Claudia!

12:48.142 --> 12:50.144
- Get your scrub ass
out of here, Ron.

12:50.144 --> 12:52.145
- Karen, stop being
a meddling bitch

12:52.145 --> 12:54.023
and tell me where Claudia is.

12:54.023 --> 12:56.317
<i>- For example, my neighbor's
alcoholic boyfriend</i>

12:56.317 --> 12:59.695
<i>literally has to be chased
away with a baseball bat.</i>

12:59.695 --> 13:02.155
<i>[mellow music]</i>

13:02.155 --> 13:03.990
- This isn't over, Karen.

13:03.990 --> 13:06.409
[tapping]
Can't hide forever, Claudia!

13:06.409 --> 13:08.037
- Do I know you?

13:08.037 --> 13:09.455
- No.

13:09.455 --> 13:11.664
- You don't know me at all?

13:11.664 --> 13:14.626
- No.
- Then what are you staring at?

13:14.626 --> 13:16.169
<i>- But we were different...</i>

13:16.169 --> 13:17.671
[door slams]

13:17.671 --> 13:19.506
<i>I thought.</i>

13:19.506 --> 13:21.716
- Sounds like working
with Renaldo at the bar

13:21.716 --> 13:23.677
wasn't such a hot idea, huh?

13:23.677 --> 13:27.972
- I mean, sure, it was
difficult to navigate at times.

13:29.892 --> 13:31.726
But it had its good parts.

13:31.726 --> 13:33.354
Beck?

13:34.730 --> 13:37.191
Beck?

13:37.191 --> 13:40.235
<i>[Hamilton Leithauser's
"Heartstruck" playing]</i>

13:40.235 --> 13:42.738
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:42.738 --> 13:46.366
<i>- ♪ Unwind ♪</i>

13:46.366 --> 13:48.744
<i>♪ Your watch ♪</i>

13:48.744 --> 13:50.538
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:50.538 --> 13:52.789
<i>♪ Shut your eyes ♪</i>

13:52.789 --> 13:53.999
<i>♪ A minute ♪</i>

13:53.999 --> 13:55.960
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:55.960 --> 13:58.671
<i>♪ 'Cause your heart ♪</i>

13:58.671 --> 14:00.880
<i>♪ Killed mine ♪</i>

14:00.880 --> 14:02.423
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:02.423 --> 14:05.177
<i>♪ And I would close ♪</i>

14:05.177 --> 14:08.972
<i>♪ The distance ♪</i>

14:08.972 --> 14:10.390
- Hi.

14:10.390 --> 14:14.436
- Hi, what is this?

14:14.436 --> 14:16.397
- I thought we could use a--

14:16.397 --> 14:18.606
a little date night.

14:18.606 --> 14:19.607
[laughs]

14:19.607 --> 14:24.697
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:24.697 --> 14:27.448
Meatball subs, your favorite.

14:27.448 --> 14:28.741
[lid clatters]

14:30.411 --> 14:33.246
Well, what do you think?

14:33.246 --> 14:35.039
- I think one errant candle

14:35.039 --> 14:38.711
could destroy an entire
collection of rare books,

14:38.711 --> 14:41.087
but...

14:41.087 --> 14:44.924
you are worth it.

14:44.924 --> 14:49.263
- [laughs]

14:49.263 --> 14:51.307
<i>[soft music]</i>

14:51.307 --> 14:53.767
I feel bad for girls
who don't eat.

14:53.767 --> 14:55.894
It always made me sad
with Peach.

14:55.894 --> 14:58.813
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:58.813 --> 15:00.399
What?

15:00.399 --> 15:02.400
- [stammers]

15:02.400 --> 15:04.611
You're talking about Peach.

15:04.611 --> 15:06.614
It's good.

15:06.614 --> 15:08.573
- Yeah.

15:08.573 --> 15:09.950
I guess so.

15:09.950 --> 15:15.456
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:15.456 --> 15:17.499
You know, I, uh,

15:17.499 --> 15:20.461
I had this Little Mermaid
sleeping bag when I was a kid.

15:20.461 --> 15:22.796
God, I loved that thing.

15:22.796 --> 15:25.131
But then it started
to smell bad,

15:25.131 --> 15:27.967
like, fungus-bad.

15:27.967 --> 15:30.638
I couldn't bring myself
to get rid of it, though.

15:30.638 --> 15:32.347
It was like--
- A security blanket.

15:32.347 --> 15:34.642
- Exactly.

15:34.642 --> 15:36.351
But then I lost it,

15:36.351 --> 15:40.105
and even though I was sad,

15:40.105 --> 15:42.149
I was kinda relieved
because I didn't--

15:42.149 --> 15:45.277
I didn't actually
have to get rid of it.

15:45.277 --> 15:47.654
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:47.654 --> 15:50.323
And it's--
it's the same with Peach.

15:50.323 --> 15:51.700
There is a part of me--

15:51.700 --> 15:53.661
oh, God, it sounds terrible.

15:53.661 --> 15:57.038
Not that I'm comparing Peach
to a cheap, nylon sleeping bag,

15:57.038 --> 15:59.625
I, uh...

15:59.625 --> 16:00.918
[laughs]

16:00.918 --> 16:03.169
This metaphor
made a lot more sense

16:03.169 --> 16:05.047
when I came to it
with Dr. Nicky.

16:06.465 --> 16:07.841
I think all this
Peach stuff is coming up

16:07.841 --> 16:09.967
because of my birthday.

16:11.427 --> 16:13.013
- December 3rd.

16:14.847 --> 16:15.849
- [laughs]

16:15.849 --> 16:17.350
You remembered?

16:17.350 --> 16:19.687
- Of course.

16:19.687 --> 16:21.312
- Anyway,

16:21.312 --> 16:26.360
Peach made such a big deal
about birthdays.

16:26.360 --> 16:29.654
And she always made sure
I felt super special

16:29.654 --> 16:33.866
and would plan
the whole thing, and...

16:33.866 --> 16:35.827
now I don't...

16:35.827 --> 16:37.203
- I'll handle it.

16:37.203 --> 16:39.206
- No, Joe--
- No, what do you want?

16:39.206 --> 16:42.668
A night at the Met?
A tasting menu at Momofuku?

16:42.668 --> 16:45.754
Hell, I'll even sing karaoke
with Annika and Lynn.

16:45.754 --> 16:48.381
- [laughs]

16:48.381 --> 16:50.341
That's sweet,
that's really...

16:50.341 --> 16:52.009
[laughs]
Really sweet.

16:52.009 --> 16:53.553
But I--

16:53.553 --> 16:56.597
I think I'd rather keep it
low-key and small.

16:57.932 --> 17:01.269
- No. No to small,
no to low-key.

17:01.269 --> 17:03.855
- [sighs]

17:03.855 --> 17:06.775
I don't know, Lynn,
Beck was pretty emphatic.

17:06.775 --> 17:10.237
- Dude, Beck's a Sagittarius.
She craves attention.

17:10.237 --> 17:12.573
This is a test, okay?
Part of the fun

17:12.573 --> 17:14.741
is making a guy think that
you don't want something

17:14.741 --> 17:16.160
and seeing if he still
comes through.

17:16.160 --> 17:17.618
- No, Beck's not like that.

17:17.618 --> 17:19.496
- Let me give you
a little lesson on Beck.

17:19.496 --> 17:21.914
Every year she wants to
"keep it simple,"

17:21.914 --> 17:24.585
and every year,
whatever guy that she's dating

17:24.585 --> 17:28.588
royally blows it, and Peach
swoops in on her Manolos

17:28.588 --> 17:30.758
and throws Beck
a party for the ages.

17:30.758 --> 17:32.925
Only now, no Peach.

17:32.925 --> 17:35.011
God rest her beautiful soul.

17:35.011 --> 17:38.432
- So you're saying
throw a party?

17:38.432 --> 17:39.932
- I'll help.

17:41.434 --> 17:43.269
I need a distraction.

17:43.269 --> 17:45.730
<i>- And I think because
I was anxious about this,</i>

17:45.730 --> 17:47.900
<i>my judgment was a little off.</i>

17:47.900 --> 17:50.402
- If I bury my sorrows
in anymore booze and boys,

17:50.402 --> 17:52.779
I'm gonna get syphilis again.

17:52.779 --> 17:55.740
And Annika is still at Esalen
on her grief retreat so--

17:55.740 --> 17:57.284
- But she didn't like Peach.

17:57.284 --> 17:59.036
- None of us liked Peach.

18:00.412 --> 18:03.248
But we loved her.

18:03.248 --> 18:06.250
Losing a friend
is super complicated, Joe.

18:06.250 --> 18:07.586
I need this.

18:07.586 --> 18:10.130
Beck needs it.

18:10.130 --> 18:12.132
<i>- Which is why I was
stupid enough</i>

18:12.132 --> 18:14.259
<i>to think Renaldo's friends
should be listened to, ever.</i>

18:14.259 --> 18:15.551
- It'll just be some friends,

18:15.551 --> 18:16.970
some NYU people.

18:16.970 --> 18:19.972
We'll make it
a surprise party, hmm?

18:19.972 --> 18:21.517
A book theme,

18:21.517 --> 18:23.101
and everyone can come dressed

18:23.101 --> 18:24.394
as their favorite
literary character.

18:24.394 --> 18:26.480
What do you say?

18:26.480 --> 18:28.981
Put it to you this way.

18:28.981 --> 18:31.108
Would you rather
do something and be wrong

18:31.108 --> 18:33.487
or nothing and be wrong?

18:33.487 --> 18:34.822
<i>- Surprise party.</i>

18:34.822 --> 18:36.490
Hmm, I thought
it would cheer him up

18:36.490 --> 18:38.659
after the death of...

18:38.659 --> 18:41.202
his beloved shih tzu.

18:41.202 --> 18:43.997
Get his mind off of things.

18:43.997 --> 18:46.290
- And?

18:46.290 --> 18:48.042
Did it?

18:48.042 --> 18:50.045
- No, it was
the beginning of the end.

18:51.505 --> 18:53.006
- Because you threw him
a surprise party?

18:53.006 --> 18:54.340
- No, no, because
that's when I realized

18:54.340 --> 18:57.009
he was cheating on me
with his therapist.

18:57.009 --> 18:59.429
<i>[eerie music]</i>

19:08.020 --> 19:10.190
[doorknob rattling,
keys clanging]

19:11.817 --> 19:13.818
[heavy steps]

19:13.818 --> 19:15.778
- Oh, shit, you scared me.

19:16.946 --> 19:18.240
- What's all this?

19:18.240 --> 19:20.867
- Uh, oh, it's my
girlfriend's birthday.

19:20.867 --> 19:22.536
Throwing her a little--
well, it's not so little.

19:22.536 --> 19:25.372
It's, um,
it's a surprise party.

19:25.372 --> 19:26.789
Kind of a literary theme.

19:26.789 --> 19:29.000
Thus...

19:30.376 --> 19:32.921
I'm going as Ernest Hemingway.

19:32.921 --> 19:34.381
"The Old Man and the Sea,"
"The Sun Also"--

19:34.381 --> 19:37.759
- I know who Hemingway is.

19:37.759 --> 19:40.220
Nice cake.

19:40.220 --> 19:42.306
She's lucky to have
a man who cares.

19:44.348 --> 19:47.394
<i>[dramatic hip-hop music]</i>

19:47.394 --> 19:49.563
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:49.563 --> 19:52.900
[indistinct chatter]

19:52.900 --> 19:54.401
[bell jingles]

19:54.401 --> 20:01.407
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:01.407 --> 20:05.746
- Bacon-wrapped date?
Bacon-wrapped date?

20:05.746 --> 20:08.080
Bacon-wrapped date?

20:08.080 --> 20:11.084
Good call.

20:11.084 --> 20:12.251
Bacon-wrapped date?

20:12.251 --> 20:14.086
- It's 9:40.

20:14.086 --> 20:15.422
Beck was supposed to be here
at 9:00 to meet for dinner.

20:15.422 --> 20:17.340
- She'll be here, relax.

20:17.340 --> 20:19.300
You know what you need,
my friend, is a drink.

20:19.300 --> 20:20.969
Hey, get this man
a Catcher in the Rye.

20:20.969 --> 20:23.512
- No, no, no, it's fine.
- She's here.

20:23.512 --> 20:25.891
Everyone hide.
Places, people.

20:25.891 --> 20:27.183
Hide!

20:27.183 --> 20:34.191
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:34.607 --> 20:37.361
all: Surprise!

20:37.361 --> 20:39.403
- How American.

20:39.403 --> 20:41.323
[laughs]

20:42.615 --> 20:45.117
- Who is that?

20:45.117 --> 20:47.453
- That's one of Beck's
school friends,

20:47.453 --> 20:49.288
I think, I don't know.

20:49.288 --> 20:50.414
I'm texting her.

20:50.414 --> 20:51.791
[phone blips]

20:51.791 --> 20:58.423
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:58.423 --> 20:59.967
What?

20:59.967 --> 21:05.513
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:05.513 --> 21:09.476
- Rude to stare,
especially in Asian cultures.

21:09.476 --> 21:11.979
Mr. Darcy, I take it?

21:11.979 --> 21:14.355
- Indeed.
- Predictable.

21:14.355 --> 21:16.148
- Says Elizabeth Bennet.

21:16.148 --> 21:17.651
- Ugh, god, no.
Dorothea Brooke.

21:17.651 --> 21:19.027
- "Middlemarch"?

21:19.027 --> 21:20.988
Named my shelter cat
after George Eliot.

21:20.988 --> 21:23.323
I love her.

21:23.323 --> 21:24.574
- The cat or the author?

21:24.574 --> 21:26.492
- Both.

21:26.492 --> 21:27.994
- Meow.

21:27.994 --> 21:30.163
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:30.163 --> 21:32.958
[big band music playing]

21:32.958 --> 21:34.250
- Hi, hey,
I'm sorry, I'm sorry,

21:34.250 --> 21:35.751
can we chat for a second?

21:35.751 --> 21:38.337
- Oh, Joe, Joe,
this is Constantine.

21:38.337 --> 21:40.257
He lives in Bushwick.

21:40.257 --> 21:41.717
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:41.717 --> 21:43.593
- That's fine.
Where the hell is Beck?

21:43.593 --> 21:45.386
- Do you wanna touch
his moustache?

21:45.386 --> 21:47.013
- No, no, no, Lynn, no, Lynn.

21:47.013 --> 21:48.515
I don't wanna
touch his moustache.

21:48.515 --> 21:50.017
- Joe.
- I don't get it.

21:50.017 --> 21:51.518
I've tried to be
the perfect boyfriend.

21:51.518 --> 21:54.395
I've bent over backwards.
I gave her a job.

21:54.395 --> 21:56.522
I threw her this party.

21:56.522 --> 21:57.523
What else can I do?

21:57.523 --> 21:59.526
- People are puzzling.

21:59.526 --> 22:01.068
Peach committed suicide,

22:01.068 --> 22:03.529
and she's the strongest
person I know--knew.

22:03.529 --> 22:05.699
- Beck isn't just puzzling,
she's impossible.

22:05.699 --> 22:07.701
Like, where is she right now?

22:07.701 --> 22:09.452
[stammers]
It's selfish.

22:09.452 --> 22:11.538
It's rude, but it's Beck...

22:11.538 --> 22:13.039
- Joe.
- And tha--

22:13.039 --> 22:15.208
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:15.208 --> 22:16.292
Oh, shit.

22:16.292 --> 22:17.711
Hi--hey!

22:19.086 --> 22:21.048
- Can I speak to you for a sec?

22:21.048 --> 22:24.800
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:24.800 --> 22:26.803
Joe, this is not
what I asked for.

22:26.803 --> 22:30.390
I said quiet,
and I said small.

22:30.390 --> 22:31.641
- Lynn said--

22:31.641 --> 22:33.059
- Oh, now you're
listening to Lynn?

22:33.059 --> 22:36.354
- In retrospect, a misfire.

22:36.354 --> 22:37.730
- Why are you wearing
a turtleneck?

22:37.730 --> 22:39.775
- I'm Hemingway--
again, misfire.

22:39.775 --> 22:42.152
- Look, I appreciate
the gesture,

22:42.152 --> 22:45.404
I just--I can't be at a party

22:45.404 --> 22:47.324
and pretend that everything
is okay without Peach.

22:47.324 --> 22:48.991
I am not a robot.

22:48.991 --> 22:50.410
- Well, what about
the other day,

22:50.410 --> 22:52.578
the relief you talked about?

22:52.578 --> 22:54.623
- Grief isn't
a straight line, Joe.

22:54.623 --> 22:57.459
- I know, you've just
been hard to read lately.

22:57.459 --> 22:58.960
- What is that
supposed to mean?

22:58.960 --> 23:00.002
- [sighs]

23:02.297 --> 23:03.798
Where were you?

23:03.798 --> 23:05.424
- Sorry?
- Beck, I called.

23:05.424 --> 23:07.469
I texted you.
- Yeah, I know.

23:07.469 --> 23:10.055
I just--my, um...

23:10.055 --> 23:12.766
my therapy session ran long.

23:12.766 --> 23:16.811
Dr. Nicky and I were
really making some headway.

23:16.811 --> 23:19.605
And then I guess I just--
I went for a walk, and...

23:19.605 --> 23:21.441
- You guess?

23:21.441 --> 23:23.567
Therapy and a walk?
- Yes.

23:23.567 --> 23:25.612
- Then why do you smell
like three glasses of rosé?

23:25.612 --> 23:28.656
- Because I sat down at some
stupid bar with my journal

23:28.656 --> 23:30.784
trying to work through shit,
Joe, that's it.

23:30.784 --> 23:32.118
- Okay so, then,
why didn't you call me?

23:32.118 --> 23:33.953
- [sighs]
I forgot.

23:33.953 --> 23:35.997
- But it's your birthday,
Beck, we made dinner plans.

23:35.997 --> 23:37.289
- [stammering]
Well, I--I just--

23:37.289 --> 23:40.292
I lost track of time.

23:40.292 --> 23:42.170
- [sighs]

23:42.170 --> 23:45.298
<i>[tense music]</i>

23:45.298 --> 23:46.799
Beck, just tell me.

23:48.468 --> 23:49.802
[whispers]
Just tell me.

23:50.804 --> 23:52.847
Tell me the truth,

23:52.847 --> 23:55.892
and we can get
through anything.

23:55.892 --> 23:59.645
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:59.645 --> 24:00.980
Okay, well,
if you can't tell me,

24:00.980 --> 24:02.148
then show me,
show me your phone.

24:02.148 --> 24:05.652
- [laughs]

24:05.652 --> 24:07.695
Are--are you
serious right now?

24:07.695 --> 24:09.655
- You said yourself, you have
a hard time with good guys.

24:09.655 --> 24:10.824
- What are you talking about?

24:10.824 --> 24:11.825
- The hootsie stuff.

24:11.825 --> 24:13.326
- [laughs]

24:13.326 --> 24:15.828
Okay, I'm--okay, fine.

24:15.828 --> 24:18.498
You wanna see my phone?

24:18.498 --> 24:20.166
Have at it.

24:20.166 --> 24:21.500
But if you do this,
it means there is

24:21.500 --> 24:24.045
absolutely no trust between us,

24:24.045 --> 24:26.798
and if we don't have trust,
we have nothing.

24:28.383 --> 24:30.009
Do you trust me?

24:30.009 --> 24:34.388
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:34.388 --> 24:36.057
You know what, I can't--

24:36.057 --> 24:37.474
I can't do this right now.

24:39.185 --> 24:41.563
Happy birthday to me.

24:41.563 --> 24:44.523
<i>[somber music]</i>

24:44.523 --> 24:51.323
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:51.323 --> 24:53.616
- ♪ Birthday to you... ♪

24:53.616 --> 24:56.452
[bell jingles]

24:56.452 --> 24:59.038
♪ Happy bir... ♪

24:59.038 --> 25:06.086
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:13.595 --> 25:16.597
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

25:16.597 --> 25:18.892
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:18.892 --> 25:22.394
- With his therapist?
You sure?

25:22.394 --> 25:24.897
That's a pretty
heavy accusation.

25:24.897 --> 25:27.275
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:27.275 --> 25:29.611
How do you know?

25:29.611 --> 25:31.070
- Experience.

25:31.070 --> 25:33.198
<i>Candace.</i>

25:33.198 --> 25:34.740
There are certain tells
you can just--

25:34.740 --> 25:37.243
you can see it in their eyes
when they look at you.

25:37.243 --> 25:39.788
- Been cheated on before?

25:39.788 --> 25:41.705
- In my last relationship.

25:41.705 --> 25:43.916
I was blind, I only saw
what I wanted to see,

25:43.916 --> 25:46.086
but I didn't make
that mistake again.

25:46.086 --> 25:49.422
This time, I made sure...

25:49.422 --> 25:52.925
that Renaldo was different.

25:52.925 --> 25:55.679
So I knew if he
was lying or cheating,

25:55.679 --> 25:57.888
someone was using him.

25:57.888 --> 25:59.891
<i>[dramatic musical thuds]</i>

25:59.891 --> 26:01.768
- Look, I'm not--I'm not
one of those shrinks

26:01.768 --> 26:03.435
that are obsessed
with the past,

26:03.435 --> 26:05.771
but I think in this case,
we should take a look.

26:05.771 --> 26:07.398
Why don't you tell me
about your childhood?

26:07.398 --> 26:08.607
- Look, I mean,
but we're not here

26:08.607 --> 26:09.858
to talk about my childhood,
right?

26:09.858 --> 26:11.278
We're talking about
my relationship.

26:11.278 --> 26:14.196
- Which ended because...
a surprise party?

26:14.196 --> 26:16.449
- No, that's not when it ended.

26:20.703 --> 26:22.955
- I brought you a donut.

26:22.955 --> 26:25.959
<i>[gentle music]</i>

26:25.959 --> 26:27.669
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:27.669 --> 26:29.503
It's glazed.

26:29.503 --> 26:33.549
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:33.549 --> 26:34.800
<i>- Wait, wait,
hold up, hold up.</i>

26:34.800 --> 26:36.677
So you're just back together

26:36.677 --> 26:38.012
regardless of your suspicions?

26:38.012 --> 26:39.431
- Eh, didn't matter.

26:39.431 --> 26:41.807
That was the past.

26:41.807 --> 26:43.977
- All right,
so what happened next?

26:43.977 --> 26:45.979
- Things were good at first.

26:45.979 --> 26:47.646
<i>But then it started to feel
like something was different.</i>

26:47.646 --> 26:51.026
- I feel like
I'm hungrier than sushi.

26:51.026 --> 26:53.819
- Okay, pizza?
- Too saucy.

26:53.819 --> 26:54.820
- Okay, Thai?

26:54.820 --> 26:56.990
- We had Thai for lunch.

26:56.990 --> 26:58.950
[phone dinging]

26:58.950 --> 27:02.328
<i>[tense music]</i>

27:02.328 --> 27:05.289
[sighs]
Why do I always have to pick?

27:05.289 --> 27:06.915
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:06.915 --> 27:08.835
- It's okay.
[phone dings]

27:08.835 --> 27:10.336
I'll choose.

27:10.336 --> 27:12.881
<i>- You're a snob, Connor.</i>

27:12.881 --> 27:16.675
<i>- It's a horrible feeling
to know things have gone wrong</i>

27:16.675 --> 27:18.635
<i>and there's nothing
you can do to change it.</i>

27:18.635 --> 27:20.137
<i>- George, I'm going to.</i>

27:20.137 --> 27:21.681
[phone dings]

27:21.681 --> 27:28.688
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:31.648 --> 27:35.069
- Mm, falafel.

27:35.069 --> 27:36.738
[phone dings]

27:36.738 --> 27:38.948
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:38.948 --> 27:43.744
<i>- You know something or
someone has come between you,</i>

27:43.744 --> 27:46.789
<i>but I had to be sure.</i>

27:46.789 --> 27:49.250
- I'll see you
after class, okay?

27:49.250 --> 27:50.417
- Okay, bye.

27:50.417 --> 27:57.467
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:05.892 --> 28:09.729
<i>Heart, heart, heart.</i>

28:12.731 --> 28:15.734
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

28:15.734 --> 28:22.741
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:29.374 --> 28:31.417
<i>I wanted to be wrong.</i>

28:31.417 --> 28:34.128
<i>I never wanted
to be wrong so badly</i>

28:34.128 --> 28:36.131
<i>in my life.</i>

28:36.131 --> 28:38.383
<i>I was begging
to be proven wrong.</i>

28:38.383 --> 28:40.218
[phone dings]

28:40.218 --> 28:42.846
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:47.224 --> 28:48.934
<i>But it was looking
like I was right.</i>

28:48.934 --> 28:55.942
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:56.984 --> 28:58.944
<i>You trust someone,</i>

28:58.944 --> 29:01.865
<i>you give them your heart,</i>

29:01.865 --> 29:03.615
<i>and what do they do?</i>

29:03.615 --> 29:06.493
<i>Is there even
a punishment that fits</i>

29:06.493 --> 29:09.788
<i>the crime of lying,
of manipulating like this,</i>

29:09.788 --> 29:12.916
<i>of breaking someone's heart?</i>

29:12.916 --> 29:15.502
<i>I guess I'm bad
at picking good people,</i>

29:15.502 --> 29:18.464
<i>but I'm good at catching
bad people red-handed.</i>

29:18.464 --> 29:25.471
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:31.853 --> 29:33.480
- Are you following me?

29:33.480 --> 29:35.105
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:40.694 --> 29:43.573
- Answer me right now.
Were you following me?

29:43.573 --> 29:46.201
- No, no, no.
I was in the neighborhood.

29:46.201 --> 29:48.327
And then I--I saw you.

29:48.327 --> 29:50.497
- God, stop lying.

29:52.164 --> 29:55.084
You know, just tell me why.

29:55.084 --> 29:56.126
Why, Joe?

29:56.126 --> 29:58.003
- It's the being late,

29:58.003 --> 29:59.213
the secret texts.

29:59.213 --> 30:00.256
You've been different, Beck.

30:00.256 --> 30:01.798
- You're being crazy.

30:01.798 --> 30:03.300
- Are you sleeping with him?

30:03.300 --> 30:04.344
- Who?

30:06.346 --> 30:07.471
- Your therapist.

30:07.471 --> 30:08.932
- [laughs]
Oh, my God.

30:08.932 --> 30:10.849
- Are you? I need to know.
I want to know.

30:10.849 --> 30:13.853
- No!
I am not sleeping with him.

30:13.853 --> 30:14.895
- Who's the fox?

30:14.895 --> 30:15.980
- What?

30:15.980 --> 30:18.900
- The fox.
The fox, Beck!

30:18.900 --> 30:22.153
- My friend,
Emma Fox, from Brown.

30:22.153 --> 30:23.779
But I guess that wasn't
readily apparent

30:23.779 --> 30:26.115
on the text from my phone, huh?

30:26.115 --> 30:29.076
<i>[soft, dramatic music]</i>

30:29.076 --> 30:31.328
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:31.328 --> 30:33.330
- Beck--
- Just don't.

30:33.330 --> 30:34.915
Joe, I told you.

30:34.915 --> 30:38.086
If we don't have trust,
we have nothing.

30:38.086 --> 30:40.255
- I know, I know, I'm sorry.

30:41.588 --> 30:42.589
- Me too.

30:45.093 --> 30:48.054
You and I are over.

30:48.054 --> 30:55.060
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:06.698 --> 31:09.284
- And that...

31:09.284 --> 31:11.536
that's when it ended.

31:11.536 --> 31:13.246
- That's one hell of a story.

31:15.539 --> 31:16.749
- What's your diagnosis?

31:16.749 --> 31:18.166
- My diagnosis?

31:18.166 --> 31:20.169
- Yeah, yeah,
what do you make of it all?

31:20.169 --> 31:22.255
- Well, you might
think I'm crazy

31:22.255 --> 31:25.758
'cause I've only known you
48 minutes, but...

31:25.758 --> 31:28.510
I think there's two of you--

31:28.510 --> 31:30.346
two Paul Browns.

31:30.346 --> 31:33.557
One has been hurt in the past.

31:33.557 --> 31:35.226
You feel betrayed and hopeless.

31:35.226 --> 31:37.394
But the other one has faith,

31:37.394 --> 31:41.857
and in spite of the evidence
to the contrary,

31:41.857 --> 31:44.943
he believes true love exists.

31:44.943 --> 31:47.070
And that is someone
I think I can help.

31:47.070 --> 31:50.032
<i>[soft, dramatic music]</i>

31:50.032 --> 31:52.035
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:52.035 --> 31:53.911
Our time is up now, but I--

31:53.911 --> 31:56.623
I would, uh, sure be down to
seeing you again if you'd like.

31:56.623 --> 32:02.170
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:02.170 --> 32:03.503
- I don't think so.

32:03.503 --> 32:10.510
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:13.597 --> 32:15.098
[door slams]

32:17.852 --> 32:21.480
<i>Everything I do,
I do to protect you, Beck.</i>

32:21.480 --> 32:23.398
[door clicks]

32:23.398 --> 32:26.402
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

32:26.402 --> 32:30.656
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:30.656 --> 32:33.284
<i>Peach, Benji--
they left me no choice.</i>

32:33.284 --> 32:35.161
<i>They were dangerous.</i>

32:35.161 --> 32:42.125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:42.125 --> 32:44.378
<i>I think you might be
in danger again.</i>

32:44.378 --> 32:51.344
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:02.438 --> 33:03.690
[elevator dings]

33:06.150 --> 33:10.904
<i>But I need
absolute proof first.</i>

33:10.904 --> 33:12.240
<i>And these days,</i>

33:12.240 --> 33:15.535
<i>the quickest way
to a man's truth</i>

33:15.535 --> 33:19.079
<i>is through his computer.</i>

33:19.079 --> 33:22.083
[doorknob rattling quietly]

33:22.083 --> 33:26.878
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:26.878 --> 33:30.758
<i>And if I find
what I'm looking for,</i>

33:30.758 --> 33:33.260
<i>Dr. Nicky will be handled.</i>

33:33.260 --> 33:40.268
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:51.820 --> 33:54.699
<i>- I mean, he followed me.</i>

33:54.699 --> 33:57.535
<i>That's just--it's not okay.</i>

33:57.535 --> 34:00.371
<i>- I get it, you feel violated.</i>

34:00.371 --> 34:01.913
<i>Pretend I'm Joe.</i>

34:01.913 --> 34:03.458
<i>What would you say to him
right now?</i>

34:05.250 --> 34:08.963
- The more you want me,
the less I want you.

34:08.963 --> 34:14.135
I know, it's messed up,
but it's true.

34:14.135 --> 34:16.762
Of course you think
I'm hiding shit.

34:16.762 --> 34:19.639
I am...

34:19.639 --> 34:24.686
hiding what a complete,
ugly mess I am.

34:24.686 --> 34:27.190
Behind this, like, cute,

34:27.190 --> 34:30.233
acceptable version
of being a mess, it's insane.

34:30.233 --> 34:32.527
<i>[soft, dramatic music]</i>

34:32.527 --> 34:34.322
I haven't dealt with this shit

34:34.322 --> 34:37.157
that went on
with me and Peach,

34:37.157 --> 34:40.702
or my dad, or Benji.

34:40.702 --> 34:42.621
And instead of putting it
into my writing,

34:42.621 --> 34:44.998
I'm hibernating with you.

34:44.998 --> 34:50.213
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:50.213 --> 34:52.172
And I resent you for it.

34:52.172 --> 34:54.592
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:54.592 --> 34:57.762
I need space to heal,

34:57.762 --> 35:00.972
but every time I turn around,
you're standing there,

35:00.972 --> 35:03.601
ready to make it all okay.

35:03.601 --> 35:05.978
But only I can do that.

35:05.978 --> 35:09.398
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:09.398 --> 35:11.608
And if you really love me,

35:11.608 --> 35:14.362
you'll see that.

35:14.362 --> 35:15.987
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:15.987 --> 35:18.032
You'll let me go.

35:18.032 --> 35:22.954
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:25.873 --> 35:27.458
<i>- Are you afraid
you might be pushing away</i>

35:27.458 --> 35:29.626
<i>a good thing, Beck?</i>

35:29.626 --> 35:32.547
<i>Do you think Joe
might be good for you?</i>

35:32.547 --> 35:34.465
<i>- Maybe.</i>

35:34.465 --> 35:37.217
<i>But it's what I need.</i>

35:37.217 --> 35:41.097
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:41.097 --> 35:43.849
<i>- That doesn't sound
like an illicit affair.</i>

35:43.849 --> 35:45.934
<i>That sounds like</i>

35:45.934 --> 35:48.771
<i>a messed-up girl in a crisis</i>

35:48.771 --> 35:52.440
<i>and a pretty decent therapist
she's lucky to have.</i>

35:52.440 --> 35:55.902
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:55.902 --> 35:58.572
<i>It also sounds like</i>

35:58.572 --> 36:01.951
<i>you were right
to end it with me.</i>

36:01.951 --> 36:06.998
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:06.998 --> 36:12.085
<i>I was wrong about all of it.</i>

36:12.085 --> 36:14.713
<i>The only thing
I wasn't wrong about</i>

36:14.713 --> 36:17.800
<i>was loving you.</i>

36:17.800 --> 36:20.594
<i>So, I'm letting you go.</i>

36:20.594 --> 36:23.264
[glass shattering]

36:23.264 --> 36:26.224
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:32.565 --> 36:34.608
[knocking]

36:38.570 --> 36:39.572
- Hey.

36:39.572 --> 36:41.574
- Hi.

36:41.574 --> 36:43.451
- Thanks for opening the door,

36:43.451 --> 36:45.911
all things considered.

36:45.911 --> 36:49.289
Uh, look,
there are a million things

36:49.289 --> 36:51.375
I could say right now,

36:51.375 --> 36:54.795
but all that matters is,
I'm sorry.

36:55.963 --> 36:58.298
- Thank you.

36:58.298 --> 37:00.259
- Jealousy got the best of me.

37:02.637 --> 37:05.389
And I, uh, I was--
I was threatened

37:05.389 --> 37:08.851
that you needed someone
to talk to who wasn't me.

37:08.851 --> 37:10.769
And I know you deserve that.

37:10.769 --> 37:12.646
You deserve
to figure your stuff out.

37:14.273 --> 37:15.815
And if I was a smarter man,

37:15.815 --> 37:20.445
maybe I wouldn't
let you go, but, um,

37:20.445 --> 37:23.114
I'm guessing that's
what you need,

37:23.114 --> 37:25.909
so I will.

37:25.909 --> 37:27.119
[box clatters]

37:30.623 --> 37:33.626
<i>[somber music]</i>

37:33.626 --> 37:35.043
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:35.043 --> 37:37.797
Goodbye, Beck.

37:37.797 --> 37:44.302
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:44.302 --> 37:45.804
- [sighs]

37:45.804 --> 37:47.556
[whispers]
Goodbye, Joe.

37:47.556 --> 37:50.476
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:50.476 --> 37:53.521
<i>- Turns out,
it is like the movies.</i>

37:53.521 --> 37:57.148
<i>The second it's over,
all you can remember</i>

37:57.148 --> 37:59.818
<i>is the stuff that
made you fall in love,</i>

37:59.818 --> 38:01.695
<i>blazing through your mind,</i>

38:01.695 --> 38:05.365
<i>this rom-com montage
made of the sweetest poison.</i>

38:05.365 --> 38:08.536
- Everythingship.

38:08.536 --> 38:10.121
I love that.

38:10.121 --> 38:11.831
<i>- I'd never felt
this way before,</i>

38:11.831 --> 38:16.210
<i>where you love the
bad things about someone</i>

38:16.210 --> 38:18.838
<i>as much as the good.</i>

38:18.838 --> 38:20.422
[train whooshing]

38:20.422 --> 38:22.675
<i>Maybe even a little more.</i>

38:22.675 --> 38:24.677
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:24.677 --> 38:27.637
<i>Love isn't
a strong enough word.</i>

38:29.597 --> 38:32.518
<i>Sometimes, it scares me</i>

38:32.518 --> 38:34.519
to love someone so completely

38:34.519 --> 38:36.521
and not have them
love you back.

38:36.521 --> 38:40.108
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:40.108 --> 38:42.027
- I'm happy to see you here.

38:42.027 --> 38:45.072
I didn't think you'd come back
after our last session.

38:45.072 --> 38:47.240
- Well, that's the thing, I...

38:47.240 --> 38:50.536
[stammers]
I don't understand it.

38:50.536 --> 38:51.871
That's why I'm here.

38:51.871 --> 38:53.371
- What don't you understand?
- Love.

38:53.371 --> 38:54.956
- [chuckles]

38:54.956 --> 38:58.335
You and 7 billion
other people on this planet.

38:58.335 --> 39:00.880
If we understood love,
I'd be out of a job.

39:00.880 --> 39:03.507
I have to say it's sort of
unique to everybody,

39:03.507 --> 39:07.094
like a fingerprint,
or a strand of DNA,

39:07.094 --> 39:09.679
or the song you lost
your virginity to.

39:11.681 --> 39:14.559
"Hungry Like the Wolf."

39:14.559 --> 39:16.394
<i>[mellow music]</i>

39:16.394 --> 39:17.896
[glass clinks]

39:17.896 --> 39:19.565
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:19.565 --> 39:22.233
<i>Some people have a hard time
letting love in.</i>

39:22.233 --> 39:25.070
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:25.070 --> 39:28.657
<i>Some people
are built for love.</i>

39:28.657 --> 39:32.327
<i>And some people
are searching,</i>

39:32.327 --> 39:34.246
<i>searching for someone
who can love them</i>

39:34.246 --> 39:36.664
<i>in the way that
they deserve.</i>

39:36.664 --> 39:38.626
<i>That's you.</i>

39:38.626 --> 39:40.418
- You look like shit.

39:40.418 --> 39:42.045
- Thanks.

39:42.045 --> 39:44.130
- What happened?

39:44.130 --> 39:47.217
- My girlfriend dumped me,
all right?

39:47.217 --> 39:49.427
So if you don't mind...

39:51.472 --> 39:54.432
<i>[mysterious percussive music]</i>

39:54.432 --> 40:01.481
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:04.777 --> 40:07.780
[both moaning]

40:07.780 --> 40:14.786
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:20.960 --> 40:23.378
- Mm.

40:23.378 --> 40:25.422
I love you, Joe.

40:27.800 --> 40:29.844
[laughs]
Your face!

40:29.844 --> 40:31.302
Oh, my God,
I was just messing with you.

40:31.302 --> 40:33.304
- Oh...
[weak laugh]

40:33.304 --> 40:35.306
[sheets ruffling]

40:35.306 --> 40:36.934
[sighs]

40:47.862 --> 40:50.864
[water running]

41:01.375 --> 41:03.293
- Are you gonna
leave Beck alone?

41:03.293 --> 41:04.460
<i>[ominous music]</i>

41:04.460 --> 41:06.338
Or will she end up like me?

41:06.338 --> 41:08.257
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:08.257 --> 41:11.260
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

41:11.260 --> 41:18.266
<i>♪ ♪</i>
